Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

**EditProductPage.xaml**
```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <!-- your form here -->
</ContentPage>
```

**EditProductPage.xaml.cs**
```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = this;
        BackCommand = new Command(async () => await OnBackRequested());
    }

    public ICommand BackCommand { get; }

    // Intercept hardware/software back button (Android, Windows)
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await OnBackRequested());
            return true; // cancel default navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed(); // allow navigation
    }

    private async Task OnBackRequested()
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            return;
        }

        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- `Shell.BackButtonBehavior` with `TextOverride="Cancel"` replaces the back arrow with a "Cancel" label and routes taps through your command.
- Override `OnBackButtonPressed()` to intercept the Android/Windows hardware/gesture back — return `true` to cancel navigation.
- On iOS, the Shell back button behavior's `Command` handles the nav bar button; the swipe-back gesture is disabled automatically when a custom `BackButtonBehavior` command is set.

Set `_hasUnsavedChanges = true` whenever a form field changes (e.g., via property setters or `TextChanged` events).
